modules.description: Provides functions to parse and serialize data structures using a custom notation, including `parse`, `serialize`, and `validate` operations. Works with nested lists, tuples, and tagged variants represented as strings. Used to convert configuration files into OCaml values and generate human-readable data dumps.

Converts various base types and compound structures into a structured representation, including units, booleans, strings, integers, floats, options, lists, and tuples of up to five elements. Works with custom types like module_name, field_name, variant_name, and var_name to build and serialize this structure. Serializes the structure into a string or pretty-prints it with optional module context.

Generates OCaml AST nodes from type representations, including pattern matching constructs, identifier names, and expression forms. Processes location data, type annotations, and string identifiers to construct syntactic elements for code transformation. Used in macro expansion to dynamically create function calls, pattern matches, and type-based expressions during compilation.
